l nerve XI"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe platysma muscle is innervated by \u003Cstrong\u003Ecranial nerve VII\u003C/strong\u003E, also known as the facial nerve. This nerve is responsible for innervating the muscles of facial expression, including the platysma. The facial nerve also carries taste sensations from the anterior two-thirds of the tongue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECranial nerve V\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the trigeminal nerve, which primarily provides sensory innervation to the face and motor innervation to the muscles of mastication.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECranial nerve VI\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the abducens nerve, which innervates the lateral rectus muscle of the eye.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECranial nerve VIII\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the vestibulocochlear nerve, responsible for hearing and balance.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECranial nerve XI\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the accessory nerve, which innervates the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The platysma muscle is innervated by the facial nerve, which is cranial nerve VII.","The facial nerve is responsible for innervating the muscles of facial expression."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58707"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18013"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58707","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58707"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T09:37:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T09:37:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10727"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73236"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4930"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Nervous System","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+1